body.description: Hello Bello Premium Baby Diapers are designed by parents, so we know first-hand that preventing leaks and blowouts is a must. Been there, done that, don't want to deal with it. We also wanted to create a diaper with ingredients we could be proud of, that was soft on sensitive skin, and was made with just as much consideration for the planet we live on as the babies we love - all at an affordable price. So that's just what we did. Featuring premium, thick leg cuffs for serious leak protection and an advanced core that quickly wicks away moisture to help minimize conditions that lead to irritation. These diapers stay snug when soiled, reducing sag and keeping a secure and comfy fit.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Hello Bello: Our Story Kristen Bell and Dax Shepard are parents who believe there is no such thing as other people’s children. (Though they reserve the right to deny that when it’s diaper duty time.) They are two of Hello Bello’s co-founders and they started the company because they believe all babies deserve the best, which means all parents need access to affordable, premium products. Hello Bello fulfills that dream. We carefully craft all of our products with babies, parents, and the planet in mind – and keep everything at low prices.

Our Mission At hello bello, we have one simple goal: to eliminate the choice many parents have to make – deciding between what’s best for their kids and best for their budget. We believe in premium for all because every baby deserves the best.
Premium leak guards for active kiddos Easy up & down with disposal tape for quick cleanup Super soft, sustainably-harvested fluff pulp Cute as the dickens designs

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They work fine. Not my personal favorite.
reviews.reviewText: These diapers are very soft and not bulky at all. They absorb fine. No problems with leaks or blowouts. The only thing I don't care for is when they're wet, they feel like Luvs. They get very gelatinous and squishy which makes me think they're fuller than they are. When I go to change the diaper, I see that it's barely wet. This may only be MY experience. So don't let this dissuade you from purchasing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great diaper for the price
reviews.reviewText: It actually hold a 3 yr olds urine all night. Very few times did he leak through from sleeping in. But the diaper seems to hold fine. They work as good as luvs. They seem to do the same job when it comes to how much they can hold. These seem to be pretty soft & comfortable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best diapers out there!
reviews.reviewText: I used Hello Bello for both of my kiddos and we absolutely love them. I have used cheaper diapers in the past but they have always lead to diaper rashes for my kiddos. I feel that hello bello diapers are just as good as the highee end brands but half the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more late night diaper runs!
reviews.reviewText: We got this subscription right after my third baby was born. We have LOVED it. The diapers don’t leak if you’re in the right size, and they have never caused irritation for baby. The wipes are unscented and nice and thick. We get just enough to last a month, and then the next box is on its way! Getting to pick the fun patterns is a bonus but it is fun to have some funky designs! We have also tried their Everywhere Balm and love it! You can get extra products that come right in your box and just get added to your monthly purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Are these knock offs?
reviews.reviewText: I've gotten hello bello before just not from Amazon and they were great. This batch seems real mediocre. The quality doesn't seem right.

reviews.reviewText: I love these diapers but the price is very high for a small amount

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Gave our baby rash
reviews.reviewText: We gave these a try and our 11 month old who has never had any diaper rash immediately got a rash and bad yeast infection. It cleared up when we went back to our old diapers - so didn't work for us.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I'm a big fan of Kristen and Dax and was excited to try these. They're thin, they're soft, but every diaper has leaked. In comparison to other brands I've tried, the leak guard wings are much shorter and thinner than other brands and the inner lining easily flips outward. I went through so many outfits the day i used these. Even when I spent the time to make sure the wings and pulled out and the flaps are in, these still leaked 😔
Love these diapers because they are way more healthy and clean than the regular diapers. And I don’t even have to pay more. They’re actually cheaper.
Loft the overall quality of Hello Bello diapers but I do find they are much more slim than say Pampers Diapers, so we’ve had a few blow outs by the legs.

I love everything about these diapers but they seem to fit small

I love the hello bello brand, but the diapers - not so much.I do continue to use them as i haven't found another brand that my daughter can tolerate, she has very sensitive skin and every other brand was leaving her with horrible, stubborn rash.But, we have atleast 2-3 blowouts a day. tried sizing up, tried rolling the back of the diaper, adjusting the waist, etc but still an ongoing issue.The blowouts happen from the back and side & it gets very messy. ruined so many sleepers because of it.
